Lines.Comment: Each word spoken like it's own sentence.
Translation: Victory!
I would destroy you if I could.
<disgusted exertion> You...
Don't think too hard. You might hurt yourself.
I'm fighting alongside you? I can't believe this...
Do not speak to me in those tones.
Do not trouble yourself. My expertise shall more than make up for your shortcomings.
Adding "new" to the Horde's name, doesn't absolve you of your sins, you know.
Oh. The Horde... and this was shaping up to be such a nice day too.
Our people were once enemies, and now we are allies. Together, we will triumph.
Despite what your kind has done to mine, I will fight beside you. Are you ready?
That is the coolest thing anyone has ever said to me.
Uh-ladies first!
For the Horde!
Lok'tar ogar!
We share an enemy. Try not to forget it.
The Horde. Of course.
The honor is mine. Lok'tar ogar, warrior!
Fight on my warriors! They cannot stop the Horde!
You will obey your warchief without question!
Today, we claim victory in the name of the Horde!
This is gonna be a blast.
Hey buddy! How you doin?
We make for a strange fellowship. But it is one I shall honor nonetheless.
Hail, friend. Your presence is most welcome.
You look way more useful than Olaf and Erik. This is going to be easy.
Oh no, it's T-T-Tomator!
